				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Both <em>Haunted</em> games use 16.8 displacements and 8.8 velocities. One drawback with 12.4 is that you may need to keep 16-bit displacements longer than you would with 16.8. In 16.8, you can ignore subpixel positions, subtract 16-bit pixel positions, reject displacements more than 128 pixels apart early, and save 8-bit pixel displacements for later processing. In 12.4, by contrast, a 20-pixel displacement between two objects is 320 units, which is solidly a 16-bit number.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

