					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">All good tricks. I think in my case, only the physics will need the fractional bits. Rendering and hit detection don't really need them.<br /><br />On a separate note, you can get cc65 to do nice loads for interleaved arrays too like this:<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">// Bad, assembly is exactly as written, no constant folding/propagation<br />for(i = 0; i &lt; 2*count; i += 2){<br />&nbsp; a = GLOBAL_ARRAY&#91;i + 0&#93;;<br />&nbsp; b = GLOBAL_ARRAY&#91;i + 2&#93;;<br />}<br /><br />// Better -&gt; tax, lda, lda<br />for(i = 0; i &lt; 2*count; i += 2){<br />&nbsp; a = (GLOBAL_ARRAY + 0)&#91;i&#93;;<br />&nbsp; b = (GLOBAL_ARRAY + 1)&#91;i&#93;;<br />}<br /></div></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

